the active class and ensuring the call site for declared methods is covered. It could be useful to check enum values for StepExecutionStatus, though I’m not sure it's necessary. I need to ensure that properties like \\\"priority,\\\" \\\"after,\\\" and \\\"uses\\\" are handled correctly within the serializer.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring JSON serialization options**\\n\\nI'm contemplating whether to use JsonInclude(NON_EMPTY) to check if the currentValue from provider.getGenerator() is empty. If the map has only ignored keys, currentValue might just be the bean. I need to test and ensure that the ignored configuration doesn't include \\\"with.\\\" But what happens if isEmpty is called and currentValue is null? It's important to consider how the custom serializer accesses provider.getGenerator() in its isEmpty checks. This might affect how I set things up.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_GxmVEIEYRGY1L9xrxAsPX2C4|fc_00c323ed16c840740169f9fe1ab67081a095ea021d43b0f345", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.keycloak/keycloak-client-common-synced/26.0.9/src/test/java/org_keycloak/keycloak_client_common_synced/MultivaluedHashMapValueSerializerTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_keycloak.keycloak_client_common_synced;\n\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.JsonNode;\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.keycloak.representations.workflows.WorkflowStepRepresentation;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class MultivaluedHashMapValueSerializerTest {\n    private final ObjectMapper mapper = new ObjectMapper();\n\n    @Test\n    void serializesOnlyConfigurationEntriesThatAreNotExposedAsStepProperties() throws Exception {\n        WorkflowStepRepresentation step = WorkflowStepRepresentation.create()\n                .of(\"reviewer-provider\")\n                .after(\"30\")\n                .withConfig(\"uses\", \"ignored-provider\")\n                .withConfig(\"priority\", \"10\")\n                .withConfig(\"enabled\", \"true\")\n                .withConfig(\"reviewers\", \"alice\", \"bob\")\n                .build();\n\n        JsonNode json = mapper.readTree(mapper.writeValueAsString(step));\n\n        assertThat(json.get(\"uses\").asText()).isEqualTo(\"reviewer-provider\");\n        assertThat(json.get(\"after\").asText()).isEqualTo(\"30\");\n        assertThat(json.has(\"priority\")).isFalse();\n\n        JsonNode config = json.get(\"with\");\n        assertThat(config.has(\"uses\")).isFalse();\n        assertThat(config.has(\"after\")).isFalse();\n        assertThat(config.has(\"priority\")).isFalse();\n        assertThat(config.get(\"enabled\").asBoolean()).isTrue();\n        assertThat(config.get(\"reviewers\")).extracting(JsonNode::asText).containsExactly(\"alice\", \"bob\");\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void treatsConfigurationAsEmptyWhenAllEntriesAreRepresentedByStepProperties() throws Exception {\n        WorkflowStepRepresentation step = WorkflowStepRepresentation.create()\n                .of(\"reviewer-provider\")\n                .after(\"30\")\n                .withConfig(\"uses\", \"ignored-provider\")\n                .build();\n\n        JsonNode json = mapper.readTree(mapper.writeValueAsString(step));\n\n        assertThat(json.get(\"uses\").asText()).isEqualTo(\"reviewer-provider\");\n        assertThat(json.get(\"after\").asText()).isEqualTo(\"30\");\n        assertThat(json.has(\"with\")).isFalse();\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1593, "output": 1181, "cacheRead": 14336, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 17110, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopR